# Git LFS is declared for large binary assets so that FUTURE commits don't add
# more weight to history. To enable the forward policy, run `git lfs install`
# once before adding new media.
#
# NOTE — honest status: the binaries already committed before this policy
# (~50 MB of full-resolution lab photos and PDF reports) are still stored
# directly in git history and are NOT in LFS; a `.gitattributes` filter does not
# migrate existing files. Shrinking the existing history requires a one-time
# `git lfs migrate import` (or git-filter-repo), which rewrites history and
# invalidates existing clones — deferred until that trade-off is accepted.
*.jpg  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.png  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.pdf  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
